commit.message:
feat(node): drop-in OpenAI compat layer matching official SDK

Compatibility layer — change one import:

    // Before: import OpenAI from 'openai';
    const { OpenAI } = require('openai-oxide/compat');

    const client = new OpenAI();
    const r = await client.chat.completions.create({ model, messages });
    const r = await client.chat.completions.parse({ model, messages, response_format: ZodSchema });
    const r = await client.responses.create({ model, input });
    for await (const chunk of await client.chat.completions.create({ ..., stream: true })) { ... }

- compat.js: OpenAI class with chat.completions, responses resources
- compat.d.ts: TypeScript types for ChatCompletion, ChatCompletionChunk, etc.
- Streaming returns async iterator (for-await compatible)
- Zod support in parse() via optional zod-to-json-schema

